---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContentHeader from '@/components/ContentHeader.astro';
import Card from '@/components/Card.astro';
import BaseLink from '@/components/BaseLink.astro';
---
<BaseLayout 
    title="Data Tool Analyzer"
    description="An interactive guide to choosing the right tool for your data needs, comparing Power Query, DuckDB, and GraphRAG."
>
    <ContentHeader
        title="Data Tool Analyzer"
        description="An interactive guide to choosing the right tool for your data needs, comparing Power Query, DuckDB, and GraphRAG."
    />

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose dark:prose-invert prose-lg space-y-8">
        <section>
            <p>In the modern data landscape, selecting the right tool for the job is critical. A tool that excels at one task may be inefficient for another. This guide provides a high-level comparison between three powerful but distinct data tools: Microsoft Power Query, DuckDB, and GraphRAG.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h3>The Contenders</h3>
            <div class="not-prose grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8">
                <Card href="/data-tools/comparison/" icon="fa-solid fa-wand-magic-sparkles" title="Power Query" blurb="The User-Friendly ETL Engine." details="Integrated into Excel and Power BI, Power Query provides a powerful visual interface for data extraction, transformation, and loading (ETL) without requiring deep coding knowledge." />
                <Card href="/data-tools/comparison/" icon="fa-solid fa-database" title="DuckDB" blurb="The In-Process Analytical Database." details="DuckDB is a high-performance analytical database that runs inside your application (e.g., Python, R, Node.js), enabling incredibly fast SQL queries on local data files like Parquet and CSV." />
                <Card href="/data-tools/comparison/" icon="fa-solid fa-share-nodes" title="GraphRAG" blurb="Context-Aware Q&A Framework." details="Graph-based Retrieval-Augmented Generation (GraphRAG) is not a single tool, but a framework that uses knowledge graphs to provide LLMs with deep, contextual information for answering complex questions." />
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mt-16">
        <BaseLink href="/data-tools/comparison/" text="View Full Comparison" style="primary" icon="fa-solid fa-arrow-right" />
    </div>
</BaseLayout>
